      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SO CAN EYE (1) could only manage to finish fifth at his latest appearance over 1609m at this track, failing to live up to market expectations. Form prior to that was far better, including a sound third over 1720m at Penrith two starts ago. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Won't find this any harder and he can bounce back to his best form. MY KGARI (3) settled in the leading division and finished well but could only manage third last start over 2240m at Melton, that effort coming on the back of a sound third at Kilmore the run before. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Taking on a better line-up this time but she good enough to play a major role. MUSICSTAR (5) must be considered after she finished third when resuming over 1609m at this track two weeks ago. CEEJAY HAICH (7) showed pleasing improvement last time out when runner-up over 1609m at this track. Each-way claims.",
